                <div class="col-md-9">
                    <img src="assets/img/hero/shoes.png" class="img-fluid rounded mb-4" alt="Hero Image">
                   <br>
                    <h4 class="section-title">Background on Athletes Foot (AF)</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">Athlete’s foot (tinea pedis) is a widespread fungal skin infection characterized
                        by redness,
                        flaking, peeling, or cracking of the skin—often between the toes or on the soles. It may itch,
                        sting, or burn, or simply feel uncomfortable. Caused by dermatophyte fungi, it thrives in warm,
                        moist environments such as locker rooms, showers, and tight footwear.</p>

                    <h4 class="section-title">Highlighting Unmet Medical Need</h4>
                    <p class="athletes">Despite affecting over 50 million Americans annually—and over a billion people
                        globally—athlete’s
                        foot remains poorly served. Before ProPedix’s Dryello, no new prescription or over the counter
                        antifungals had been developed to combat athlete’s foot since the 1980s, leaving patients
                        dissatisfied and with their symptoms persisting.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        These outdated treatments fail to address the true root cause of the infection, and as a result,
                        many patients don’t seek treatment at all, discouraged by the limited options available.
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        The athlete’s foot market today is large, fragmented, and under-optimized—representing a $6B+
                        global TAM. While primarily OTC, it includes hundreds of undifferentiated products and very few
                        established brands. Even as the market landscape has shifted dramatically in these last five
                        years, first-line treatments have remained unchanged. That is why ProPedix is dedicated to
                        providing an innovative solution that delivers both clinical efficacy and a better patient
                        experience so that you can stick it to athlete’s foot.
                    </p>

